theorem interior_closure_diff_self_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X) \ A) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  classical
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hxInt
    rcases mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.1 hxInt with
      ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset⟩
    -- `x` lies in `closure A` because `U ⊆ closure A \ A`.
    have hx_closure : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := by
      have : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) \ A := hU_subset hxU
      exact this.1
    -- Since `A` is dense in its closure, `U` meets `A`.
    have h_nonempty : ((U : Set X) ∩ (A : Set X)).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff.1 hx_closure) U hU_open hxU
    -- But `U ⊆ closure A \ A`, hence `U ∩ A = ∅`, contradiction.
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, hyU, hyA⟩
    have : (y : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) \ A := hU_subset hyU
    exact (this.2 hyA).elim
  · exact Set.empty_subset _

theorem closure_diff_eq_self_inter_compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (A : Set X) \ A = closure (A : Set X) ∩ (A : Set X)ᶜ := by
  rfl
